### Data Sources (S3-backed)
Data is synced from Google Sheets to AWS S3 every 30 minutes via Lambda, then served through Vercel API endpoints.

| Data | S3 File | API Endpoint | Source Google Sheet Tab |
|------|---------|--------------|-------------------------|
| Traffic Monthly | `traffic-data.csv` | `/api/data/traffic` | Traffic Monthly |
| Traffic Average | `internal-average-traffic.csv` | `/api/data/average` | Traffic Average |
| DR History | `DR History.csv` | `/api/data/dr` | DR |
| RD History | `RD History.csv` | `/api/data/rd` | RD |
| Revenue | `revenue-history.csv` | `/api/data/revenue` | Revenue |

**Priority CSV files (for faster dashboard load):**
Lambda also generates filtered versions containing only top ~200 domains (by revenue):

| Data | S3 File | API Endpoint | Size Reduction |
|------|---------|--------------|----------------|
| Traffic Priority | `traffic-data-priority.csv` | `/api/data/traffic-priority` | ~14MB → ~500KB |
| Average Priority | `internal-average-traffic-priority.csv` | `/api/data/average-priority` | Similar |
| DR Priority | `DR History-priority.csv` | `/api/data/dr-priority` | ~7.5MB → ~300KB |
| RD Priority | `RD History-priority.csv` | `/api/data/rd-priority` | Similar |

The main dashboard (`index-apex.html`) fetches priority files first with fallback to full files. Leaderboard/agent/niche pages still use full files since they display all domains.

**Local files (not synced):**
- `ahrefs_organic_traffic_results.csv` - Ahrefs organic traffic (loaded directly)
- `ahrefs-average-traffic.csv` - Ahrefs average traffic (loaded directly)
- `Site Agent & Niche.csv` - Agent/niche mappings (loaded directly)

**Note:** Revenue CSV uses "Current" as column header for the current month instead of "Jan 2026" format. The dashboard dynamically maps "Current" to whatever the actual current month is.

